claim.claim-text:
1. A waste water inspecting agent used as an additive to a specimen solution comprising: 
a rod-shaped body; 
a capturing structured element bonded to the rod-shaped body which specifically captures an object to be captured in a specimen solution.

19. A waste water inspecting apparatus comprising: 
a waste water inspecting agent; 
means for contacting the waste water inspecting agent to the specimen solution; and 
means for measuring a change in wavelength of a colored interference light reflected by the waste water inspecting agent capturing the object to be captured; 
wherein the waste water inspecting agent comprises a rod-shaped body having a length of 810 nm or less and a capturing structured element bonded to the rod shaped body for specifically capturing an object to be captured and contained in a specimen solution and which reflects an incident light as colored interference light by aligning in a film-like shape.

21. A waste water inspecting apparatus comprising: 
a biosensor which comprises one of a quartz oscillator and a surface acoustic wave (SAW) element and a waste water inspecting agent aligned to the one of a quartz oscillator and a surface acoustic wave (SAW) element in a film-like shape; 
an oscillation circuit which oscillates one of a change in mass and a change in viscoelasticity as a frequency when the biosensor captures an object to be captured; and 
a frequency counter which measures the frequency of the oscillation oscillated by the oscillation circuit; 
wherein the waste water inspecting agent comprises a rod-shaped body and a capturing structured element bonded to the rod-shaped body which specifically captures an object to be captured in a specimen solution and the waste water inspecting agent is amphiphilic.
